<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,932,1319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,932,958]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[767,831,933,959]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Japan</collectingCountry>
and is so far known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1131,1195,933,959]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1210,1322,932,958]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
and Honshu), 
<collectingCountry box="[213,281,969,995]" name="South Korea" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Korea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[336,403,968,994]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[417,672,968,994]" country="China" name="Heilongjiang" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Heilongjiang Province</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[725,945,968,995]" country="China" name="Shandong" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Shandong Province</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Miyamoto, S. &amp; Yasunaga, T." box="[967,1300,968,995]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" pagination="151 - 188" refId="ref8910" refString="Miyamoto, S. &amp; Yasunaga, T. (1989) Hemiptera, Heteroptera. In: Hirashima, Y., Morimoto, K. &amp; Tadauchi, O. (Eds.), A check list of Japanese insects. Kyushu University, Fukuoka, pp. 151 - 188. [in Japanese]" type="book chapter" year="1989">Miyamoto &amp; Yasunaga, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; Lee, Kown &amp; Miyamoto, 1993; 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q." box="[381,569,1004,1030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref8869" refString="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q. (1998) On the genus Megalotomus Fieber from China (Heteroptera: Alydidae). Entomologische Berichten, Amsterdam, 58 (3), 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="1998">Liu &amp; Liu, 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,932,1319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">
Specimens were rather limited which made the study of some morphological characters difficult. Based on published information, this species resembles 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[683,810,1077,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="junceus">
<emphasis box="[683,810,1077,1102]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">M. junceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in body size and colour, but differs from it and other 
<taxonomicName box="[151,391,1112,1138]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis box="[151,303,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Megalotomus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the male genital structures. As noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer, C. W. &amp; Schaffner, J. C. &amp; Ahmad, I." box="[871,1100,1112,1139]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" pagination="500 - 507" refId="ref9311" refString="Schaefer, C. W., Schaffner, J. C. &amp; Ahmad, I. (1989) The Alydus - group, with Notes on the Alydine Genital Capsule (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Alydidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 82 (4), 500 - 507. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 82.4.500" type="journal article" year="1989">
Schaefer 
<emphasis box="[975,1031,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
, 1989
</bibRefCitation>
on page 503, the “surcapsular spine extending beyond end of capsule, each spine with small spine arising middorsally; spine more narrow and straighter”. These characteristics were also illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q." box="[801,994,1184,1210]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref8869" refString="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q. (1998) On the genus Megalotomus Fieber from China (Heteroptera: Alydidae). Entomologische Berichten, Amsterdam, 58 (3), 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="1998">Liu &amp; Liu (1998</bibRefCitation>
: see illustration of fig 17, on page 43). However, the surcapsular spines illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q." box="[671,865,1220,1246]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref8869" refString="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q. (1998) On the genus Megalotomus Fieber from China (Heteroptera: Alydidae). Entomologische Berichten, Amsterdam, 58 (3), 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="1998">Liu &amp; Liu (1998)</bibRefCitation>
crossed each other at the apex, which was contrary to other 
<taxonomicName box="[244,492,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[244,396,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Megalotomus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,932,1319]" box="[199,1028,1292,1319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">This species should be studied further once more specimens are collected.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
